  "body": "### Description\r\nBesu has poor performance for tracing blocks / transactions\r\n\r\nAs an user I want to be able to trace blocks and transactions reliably and quickly without OOM errors or hitting timeouts on the RPC layer so that I can get the info I need for my use-case. \r\n\r\nWill be needed to support ANY rollups use-case. \r\n\r\nRelated to #3786\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Queries return quickly: [#4672](https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/issues/4672)\r\n* Queries do not OOM \r\n* Queries do not timeout \r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\n* Not sure why we are slow \r\n* Many times Besu would crash when tracing a full block \r\n* OOM errors eg #4050 \r\n* Short timeout can cause issues - some blocks take 10+ min to trace\r\n\r\n### Potential Approach \r\n\r\n* Solution?: Instead of replaying each time the traces for each user request, why not saving this trace result (could generate at the time of block creation?) in a separate database of a separate module instead of saving the block and the worldstate for each block\r\n* Solution?: Separate into a different microservice\r\nSeparate the query part of Besu into a completely separate process. Queries that are asking Besu questions related to chain do not need to slow down the main flow.\r\n\r\n\r\n**NEED SCOPING / TIMING ESTIMATE**",
